8273591827327, \"rank\": 0.0017284724493723234, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"accusations\", \"from\": 1678, \"to\": 1689}, {\"ngram\": \"some national associations\", \"from\": 1695, \"to\": 1721}, {\"ngram\": \"cover-ups\", \"from\": 1737, \"to\": 1746}, {\"ngram\": \"fake news\", \"from\": 1763, \"to\": 1772}, {\"ngram\": \"replies\", \"from\": 1774, \"to\": 1781}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While there is anger after the doping agency cleared the Chinese swimmers but banned Russian figure skater Kamila Valieva, who also claimed contamination with TMZ before competing at the Beijing 2022 Winter Games.\", \"from\": 1792, \"to\": 2005, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1849, \"end\": 1856, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9978782890361554, \"rank\": 0.0021099362914198797, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1877, \"end\": 1884, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"score\": 0.9998981689910669, \"rank\": 9.886764268760535e-05, \"text\": \"Russian\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Russia\"}, {\"begin\": 1899, \"end\": 1905, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamila_Thompson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kamila\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamila_Thompson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kamila_Thompson\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"anger\", \"from\": 1807, \"to\": 1812}, {\"ngram\": \"the doping agency\", \"from\": 1819, \"to\": 1836}, {\"ngram\": \"contamination\", \"from\": 1932, \"to\": 1945}, {\"ngram\": \"TMZ\", \"from\": 1951, \"to\": 1954}, {\"ngram\": \"the Beijing 2022 Winter Games\", \"from\": 1975, \"to\": 2004}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Here's how the scandal came to light and what we know ahead ofthe Paris Olympics: On 22 April of this year, Wada, courtesy of Ross Wenzel, general counsel and a former outside lawyer at the time, detailed the series of events from 2021.\", \"from\": 2006, \"to\": 2243, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2072, \"end\": 2086, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Paris Olympics\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1924_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 2133, \"end\": 2137, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ross_Geller\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 5.296350429385869e-12, \"text\": \"Ross\", \"types\": [\"Q95074\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ross_Geller\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ross_Geller\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the scandal\", \"from\": 2017, \"to\": 2028}, {\"ngram\": \"light\", \"from\": 2037, \"to\": 2042}, {\"ngram\": \"22 April\", \"from\": 2091, \"to\": 2099}, {\"ngram\": \"this year\", \"from\": 2103, \"to\": 2112}, {\"ngram\": \"Wada\", \"from\": 2114, \"to\": 2118}, {\"ngram\": \"courtesy\", \"from\": 2120, \"to\": 2128}, {\"ngram\": \"general counsel\", \"from\": 2145, \"to\": 2160}, {\"ngram\": \"a former outside lawyer\", \"from\": 2165, \"to\": 2188}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 2192, \"to\": 2200}, {\"ngram\": \"the series\", \"from\": 2211, \"to\": 2221}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 2225, \"to\": 2231}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wenzel stated that Chinese anti-doping authorities collected 60 urine samples at a national swimming meet on 3 January, 2021.\", \"from\": 2245, \"to\": 2370, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2264, \"end\": 2271, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9978782890361554, \"rank\": 0.0021099362914198797, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wenzel\", \"from\": 2245, \"to\": 2251}, {\"ngram\": \"60 urine samples\", \"from\": 2306, \"to\": 2322}, {\"ngram\": \"a national swimming meet\", \"from\": 2326, \"to\": 2350}, {\"ngram\": \"3 January\", \"from\": 2354, \"to\": 2363}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On 15 March, Chinada told Wada that it had discovered 28 positive tests.\", \"from\": 2371, \"to\": 2443, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"15 March\", \"from\": 2374, \"to\": 2382}, {\"ngram\": \"Chinada\", \"from\": 2384, \"to\": 2391}, {\"ngram\": \"Wada\", \"from\": 2397, \"to\": 2401}, {\"ngram\": \"28 positive tests\", \"from\": 2425, \"to\": 2442}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In May, Chinada stated it had found trace amounts of the banned substance at a hotel where all 23 athletes were staying.\", \"from\": 2445, \"to\": 2565, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"May\", \"from\": 2448, \"to\": 2451}, {\"ngram\": \"Chinada\", \"from\": 2453, \"to\": 2460}, {\"ngram\": \"trace amounts\", \"from\": 2481, \"to\": 2494}, {\"ngram\": \"the banned substance\", \"from\": 2498, \"to\": 2518}, {\"ngram\": \"a hotel\", \"from\": 2522, \"to\": 2529}, {\"ngram\": \"all 23 athletes\", \"from\": 2536, \"to\": 2551}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Notably the trace amounts were reportedly found in spice containers in the hotel kitchen and drainage units.\", \"from\": 2566, \"to\": 2674, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the trace amounts\", \"from\": 2574, \"to\": 2591}, {\"ngram\": \"spice containers\", \"from\": 2617, \"to\": 2633}, {\"ngram\": \"the hotel kitchen\", \"from\": 2637, \"to\": 2654}, {\"ngram\": \"drainage units\", \"from\": 2659, \"to\": 2673}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It informed Wada on 15 June that it would not be charging the swimmers with anti-doping violations, stating that the positive tests were caused by contamination.\", \"from\": 2676, \"to\": 2837, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wada\", \"from\": 2688, \"to\": 2692}, {\"ngram\": \"15 June\", \"from\": 2696, \"to\": 2703}, {\"ngram\": \"the swimmers\", \"from\": 2734, \"to\": 2746}, {\"ngram\": \"anti-doping violations\", \"from\": 2752, \"to\": 2774}, {\"ngram\": \"the positive tests\", \"from\": 2789, \"to\": 2807}, {\"ngram\": \"contamination\", \"from\": 2823, \"to\": 2836}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Trimetazidine, or TMZ, can be used to treat angina and other heart-related conditions.\", \"from\": 2839, \"to\": 2925, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Trimetazidine\", \"from\": 2839, \"to\": 2852}, {\"ngram\": \"TMZ\", \"from\": 2857, \"to\": 2860}, {\"ngram\": \"angina\", \"from\": 2883, \"to\": 2889}, {\"ngram\": \"other heart-related conditions\", \"from\": 2894, \"to\": 2924}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It has been on Wada's prohibited substances list since 2014 given its potential to improve endurance and blood flow.\", \"from\": 2926, \"to\": 3042, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wada's prohibited substances list\", \"from\": 2941, \"to\": 2974}, {\"ngram\": \"its potential\", \"from\": 2992, \"to\": 3005}, {\"ngram\": \"endurance\", \"from\": 3017, \"to\": 3026}, {\"ngram\": \"blood flow\", \"from\": 3031, \"to\": 3041}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wenzel said in his investigation that Chinada did not get individual testimonies from the 23 Chinese swimmers about how the substance appeared in their samples.\", \"from\": 3044, \"to\": 3204, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3137, \"end\": 3144, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9978782890361554, \"rank\": 0.0021099362914198797, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wenzel\", \"from\": 3044, \"to\": 3050}, {\"ngram\": \"his investigation\", \"from\": 3059, \"to\": 3076}, {\"ngram\": \"Chinada\", \"from\": 3082, \"to\": 3089}, {\"ngram\": \"individual testimonies\", \"from\": 3102, \"to\": 3124}, {\"ngram\": \"the substance\", \"from\": 3164, \"to\": 3177}, {\"ngram\": \"their samples\", \"from\": 3190, \"to\": 3203}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Athletes who claim contamination usually must provide an explanation for the potential or likely source of contamination.\", \"from\": 3205, \"to\": 3326, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Athletes\", \"from\": 3205, \"to\": 3213}, {\"ngram\": \"contamination\", \"from\": 3224, \"to\": 3237}, {\"ngram\": \"an explanation\", \"from\": 3259, \"to\": 3273}, {\"ngram\": \"the potential or likely source\", \"from\": 3278, \"to\": 3308}, {\"ngram\": \"contamination\", \"from\": 3312, \"to\": 3325}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wenzel said Chinada \\\"did not hypothesize in their report\\\" why trace amounts of a banned heart medication were found in the kitchen of a hotel where elite swimmers were staying during competition.\", \"from\": 3328, \"to\": 3523, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wenzel\", \"from\": 3328, \"to\": 3334}, {\"ngram\": \"Chinada\", \"from\": 3340, \"to\": 3347}, {\"ngram\": \"their report\", \"from\": 3372, \"to\": 3384}, {\"ngram\": \"why trace amounts\", \"from\": 3386, \"to\": 3403}, {\"ngram\": \"a banned heart medication\", \"from\": 3407, \"to\": 3432}, {\"ngram\": \"the kitchen\", \"from\": 3447, \"to\": 3458}, {\"ngram\": \"a hotel\", \"from\": 3462, \"to\": 3469}, {\"ngram\": \"elite swimmers\", \"from\": 3476, \"to\": 3490}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 3511, \"to\": 3522}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"The ultimate source, meaning how the TMZ got into the kitchen, was not discovered,\\\" Wenzel said.\", \"from\": 3525, \"to\": 3622, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3563, \"end\": 3566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.4791602192922355e-26, \"text\": \"TMZ\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/TMZ\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The ultimate source\", \"from\": 3526, \"to\": 3545}, {\"ngram\": \"the kitchen\", \"from\": 3576, \"to\": 3587}, {\"ngram\": \"Wenzel\", \"from\": 3610, \"to\": 3616}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wada officials said that due to the widespread cases of Covid-19 in the region at the time, an investigation in China was not possible.\", \"from\": 3624, \"to\": 3759, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3736, \"end\": 3741, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.998273591827327, \"rank\": 0.0017284724493723234, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wada officials\", \"from\": 3624, \"to\": 3638}, {\"ngram\": \"the widespread cases\", \"from\": 3656, \"to\": 3676}, {\"ngram\": \"Covid-19\", \"from\": 3680, \"to\": 3688}, {\"ngram\": \"the region\", \"from\": 3692, \"to\": 3702}, {\"ngram\": \"the time\", \"from\": 3706, \"to\": 3714}, {\"ngram\": \"an investigation\", \"from\": 3716, \"to\": 3732}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wada investigated the circumstances and ruled out the prospect of microdosing, while also maintaining that the positive tests were limited to the athletes, according to Chinada, who stayed at the same hotel.\", \"from\": 3761, \"to\": 3968, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wada\", \"from\": 3761, \"to\": 3765}, {\"ngram\": \"the circumstances\", \"from\": 3779, \"to\": 3796}, {\"ngram\": \"the prospect\", \"from\": 3811, \"to\": 3823}, {\"ngram\": \"microdosing\", \"from\": 3827, \"to\": 3838}, {\"ngram\": \"the positive tests\", \"from\": 3868, \"to\": 3886}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 3903, \"to\": 3915}, {\"ngram\": \"Chinada\", \"from\": 3930, \"to\": 3937}, {\"ngram\": \"the same hotel\", \"from\": 3953, \"to\": 3967}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"All of those athletes were in the same place at the same time when the positives arose, and all of these sample results were at consistently low levels,\\\" Wenzel said.\", \"from\": 3970, \"to\": 4137, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"those athletes\", \"from\": 3978, \"to\": 3992}, {\"ngram\": \"the same place\", \"from\": 4001, \"to\": 4015}, {\"ngram\": \"the same time\", \"from\": 4019, \"to\": 4032}, {\"ngram\": \"the positives\", \"from\": 4038, \"to\": 4051}, {\"ngram\": \"these sample results\", \"from\": 4070, \"to\": 4090}, {\"ngram\": \"consistently low levels\", \"from\": 4099, \"to\": 4122}, {\"ngram\": \"Wenzel\", \"from\": 4125, \"to\": 4131}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wada had the option to challenge Chinada at the Court of Arbitration for Sport (CAS), but ultimately decided in July not to do so due to insufficient evidence and legal advice surrounding the likelihood of disproving the explanation of contamination.\", \"from\": 4139, \"to\": 4389, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wada\", \"from\": 4139, \"to\": 4143}, {\"ngram\": \"the option\", \"from\": 4148, \"to\": 4158}, {\"ngram\": \"Chinada\", \"from\": 4172, \"to\": 4179}, {\"ngram\": \"the Court\", \"from\": 4183, \"to\": 4192}, {\"ngram\": \"Arbitration\", \"from\": 4196, \"to\": 4207}, {\"ngram\": \"Sport\", \"from\": 4212, \"to\": 4217}, {\"ngram\": \"CAS\", \"from\": 4219, \"to\": 4222}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 4251, \"to\": 4255}, {\"ngram\": \"insufficient evidence\", \"from\": 4276, \"to\": 4297}, {\"ngram\": \"legal advice\", \"from\": 4302, \"to\": 4314}, {\"ngram\": \"the likelihood\", \"from\": 4327, \"to\": 4341}, {\"ngram\": \"the explanation\", \"from\": 4356, \"to\": 4371}, {\"ngram\": \"contamination\", \"from\": 4375, \"to\": 4388}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wada considered the athletes innocent and did not publicly reveal details of the case before the Tokyo Olympics, where China's 30-person swimming team won six medals, including three golds.\", \"from\": 4391, \"to\": 4580, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4510, \"end\": 4515, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.998273591827327, \"rank\": 0.0017284724493723234, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wada\", \"from\": 4391, \"to\": 4395}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 4407, \"to\": 4419}, {\"ngram\": \"details\", \"from\": 4457, \"to\": 4464}, {\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 4468, \"to\": 4476}, {\"ngram\": \"the Tokyo Olympics\", \"from\": 4484, \"to\": 4502}, {\"ngram\": \"six medals\", \"from\": 4546, \"to\": 4556}, {\"ngram\": \"three golds\", \"from\": 4568, \"to\": 4579}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Given the presumption of innocence, the national anti-doping body can determine no violation and is not under any obligation to publicly reveal details of a case.\", \"from\": 4582, \"to\": 4744, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the presumption\", \"from\": 4588, \"to\": 4603}, {\"ngram\": \"innocence\", \"from\": 4607, \"to\": 4616}, {\"ngram\": \"the national anti-doping body\", \"from\": 4618, \"to\": 4647}, {\"ngram\": \"no violation\", \"from\": 4662, \"to\": 4674}, {\"ngram\": \"any obligation\", \"from\": 4692, \"to\": 4706}, {\"ngram\": \"details\", \"from\": 4726, \"to\": 4733}, {\"ngram\": \"a case\", \"from\": 4737, \"to\": 4743}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wada would only publicly discuss a case if Chinada did so or it intended to take the case to CAS.\", \"from\": 4745, \"to\": 4842, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4838, \"end\": 4841, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.8638140632421904e-57, \"text\": \"CAS\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Court_of_Arbitration_for_Sport\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wada\", \"from\": 4745, \"to\": 4749}, {\"ngram\": \"a case\", \"from\": 4778, \"to\": 4784}, {\"ngram\": \"Chinada\", \"from\": 4788, \"to\": 4795}, {\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 4826, \"to\": 4834}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wada president Witold Banka said: \\\"It's a question about whether you want or not to expose the innocent athletes, right?\", \"from\": 4844, \"to\": 4964, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4859, \"end\": 4865, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vytautas\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.2351786825251884e-22, \"text\": \"Witold\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vytautas\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Vytautas\"}, {\"begin\": 4866, \"end\": 4871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bangka_Island\", \"score\": 0.9849089956434262, \"rank\": 0.015297091330731394, \"text\": \"Banka\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bangka_Island\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bangka_Island\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a question\", \"from\": 4884, \"to\": 4894}, {\"ngram\": \"the innocent athletes\", \"from\": 4935, \"to\": 4956}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We have to take into account that through publishing the names of athletes without anti-doping rule violations, you expose the innocent athletes and you can damage their image.\", \"from\": 4965, \"to\": 5141, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"account\", \"from\": 4986, \"to\": 4993}, {\"ngram\": \"the names\", \"from\": 5018, \"to\": 5027}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 5031, \"to\": 5039}, {\"ngram\": \"anti-doping rule violations\", \"from\": 5048, \"to\": 5075}, {\"ngram\": \"the innocent athletes\", \"from\": 5088, \"to\": 5109}, {\"ngram\": \"their image\", \"from\": 5129, \"to\": 5140}]}, {\"sentence\": \"So this is a discussion which is very important, and our role is to protect innocent athletes as well.\\\"\", \"from\": 5142, \"to\": 5245, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a discussion\", \"from\": 5153, \"to\": 5165}, {\"ngram\": \"our role\", \"from\": 5195, \"to\": 5203}, {\"ngram\": \"innocent athletes\", \"from\": 5218, \"to\": 5235}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The scandal led to an independent investigation, which concluded in July 2024 that Wada did not show bias in the case of 23 Chinese swimmers cleared to compete in Tokyo, despite the athletes testing positive for a banned substance.\", \"from\": 5247, \"to\": 5478, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5371, \"end\": 5378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9978782890361554, \"rank\": 0.0021099362914198797, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 5410, \"end\": 5415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999875913091, \"rank\": 1.2408536472806257e-08, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo_bid_for_the_2020_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The scandal\", \"from\": 5247, \"to\": 5258}, {\"ngram\": \"an independent investigation\", \"from\": 5266, \"to\": 5294}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 5315, \"to\": 5319}, {\"ngram\": \"Wada\", \"from\": 5330, \"to\": 5334}, {\"ngram\": \"bias\", \"from\": 5348, \"to\": 5352}, {\"ngram\": \"the case\", \"from\": 5356, \"to\": 5364}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 5425, \"to\": 5437}, {\"ngram\": \"a banned substance\", \"from\": 5459, \"to\": 5477}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Swiss prosecutor Eric Cottier's interim report also stated that it was reasonable for Wada not to appeal the decision by Chinada to not punish the athletes.\", \"from\": 5480, \"to\": 5636, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5480, \"end\": 5485, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9633091455995804, \"rank\": 0.03808834745755286, \"text\": \"Swiss\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wada\", \"from\": 5566, \"to\": 5570}, {\"ngram\": \"the decision\", \"from\": 5585, \"to\": 5597}, {\"ngram\": \"Chinada\", \"from\": 5601, \"to\": 5608}, {\"ngram\": \"the athletes\", \"from\": 5623, \"to\": 5635}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wada's senior director of science and medicine, Olivier Rabin, had \\\"doubts about the reality of contamination as described by the Chinese authorities,\\\" according to the annex to Cottier's report.\", \"from\": 5638, \"to\": 5833, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 5768, \"end\": 5775, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9978782890361554, \"rank\": 0.0021099362914198797, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wada's senior director\", \"from\": 5638, \"to\": 5660}, {\"ngram\": \"science\", \"from\": 5664, \"to\": 5671}, {\"ngram\": \"medicine\", \"from\": 5676, \"to\": 5684}, {\"ngram\": \"Olivier Rabin\", \"from\": 5686, \"to\": 5699}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\"doubts\", \"from\": 5705, \"to\": 5712}, {\"ngram\": \"the reality\", \"from\": 5719, \"to\": 5730}, {\"ngram\": \"contamination\", \"from\": 5734, \"to\": 5747}, {\"ngram\": \"the annex\", \"from\": 5803, \"to\": 5812}, {\"ngram\": \"Cottier's report\", \"from\": 5816, \"to\": 5832}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But no action was taken due to being \\\"unable to exclude the contamination scenario in a solidly substantiated manner\\\" and ultimately he \\\"saw no other solution than to accept it\\\".\", \"from\": 5835, \"to\": 6013, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no action\", \"from\": 5839, \"to\": 5848}, {\"ngram\": \"the contamination scenario\", \"from\": 5891, \"to\": 5917}, {\"ngram\": \"a solidly substantiated manner\", \"from\": 5921, \"to\": 5951}, {\"ngram\": \"no other solution\", \"from\": 5976, \"to\": 5993}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wada also explained that it was \\\"not in a position to disprove\\\" Chinada's story with independent experts and external legal counsel helping to inform the decision to not appeal.\", \"from\": 6015, \"to\": 6192, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Wada\", \"from\": 6015, \"to\": 6019}, {\"ngram\": \"a position\", \"from\": 6055, \"to\": 6065}, {\"ngram\": \"\\\" Chinada's story\", \"from\": 6077, \"to\": 6094}, {\"ngram\": \"independent experts\", \"from\": 6100, \"to\": 6119}, {\"ngram\": \"external legal counsel\", \"from\": 6124, \"to\": 6146}, {\"ngram\": \"the decision\", \"from\": 6165, \"to\": 6177}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The scandal has seenMichael Phelps, Adam Peaty, Katie Ledecky and others hit out at the anti-doping body with fears that trust has been lost among athletes ahead of the biggest swimming meet of the four-year cycle.\", \"from\": 6194, \"to\": 6408, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6222, \"end\": 6228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.634428629131151e-15, \"text\": \"Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\"}, {\"begin\": 6230, \"end\": 6240, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Adam Peaty\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Adam_Peaty\"}, {\"begin\": 6242, \"end\": 6255, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Katie Ledecky\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Katie_Ledecky\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The scandal\", \"from\": 6194, \"to\": 6205}, {\"ngram\": \"others\", \"from\": 6260, \"to\": 6266}, {\"ngram\": \"the anti-doping body\", \"from\": 6278, \"to\": 6298}, {\"ngram\": \"fears\", \"from\": 6304, \"to\": 6309}, {\"ngram\": \"trust\", \"from\": 6315, \"to\": 6320}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 6341, \"to\": 6349}, {\"ngram\": \"the biggest swimming meet\", \"from\": 6359, \"to\": 6384}, {\"ngram\": \"the four-year cycle\", \"from\": 6388, \"to\": 6407}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Phelps said athletes can no longer place their faith in Wada: \\\"As athletes, our faith can no longer be blindly placed in the World Anti-Doping Agency, an organisation that continues to prove that it is either incapable or unwilling to enforce its policies consistently around the world,\\\" Phelps said.\", \"from\": 6410, \"to\": 6710, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6410, \"end\": 6416, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.634428629131151e-15, \"text\": \"Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\"}, {\"begin\": 6698, \"end\": 6704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 8.634428629131151e-15, \"text\": \"Phelps\", \"types\": [\"Q901\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/William_H._Phelps_Sr.\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 6422, \"to\": 6430}, {\"ngram\": \"their faith\", \"from\": 6451, \"to\": 6462}, {\"ngram\": \"Wada\", \"from\": 6466, \"to\": 6470}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 6476, \"to\": 6484}, {\"ngram\": \"our faith\", \"from\": 6486, \"to\": 6495}, {\"ngram\": \"the World Anti-Doping Agency\", \"from\": 6531, \"to\": 6559}, {\"ngram\": \"an organisation\", \"from\": 6561, \"to\": 6576}, {\"ngram\": \"its policies\", \"from\": 6653, \"to\": 6665}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 6686, \"to\": 6695}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It is clear to me that any attempts of reform at Wada have fallen short, and there are still deeply rooted, systemic problems that prove detrimental to the integrity of international sports and athletes' right to fair competition, time and time again.\\\"\", \"from\": 6712, \"to\": 6965, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"any attempts\", \"from\": 6736, \"to\": 6748}, {\"ngram\": \"reform\", \"from\": 6752, \"to\": 6758}, {\"ngram\": \"Wada\", \"from\": 6762, \"to\": 6766}, {\"ngram\": \"deeply rooted, systemic problems\", \"from\": 6806, \"to\": 6838}, {\"ngram\": \"the integrity\", \"from\": 6865, \"to\": 6878}, {\"ngram\": \"international sports\", \"from\": 6882, \"to\": 6902}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes' right\", \"from\": 6907, \"to\": 6922}, {\"ngram\": \"fair competition\", \"from\": 6926, \"to\": 6942}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 6944, \"to\": 6948}, {\"ngram\": \"time\", \"from\": 6953, \"to\": 6957}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Travis Tygart, CEO of the United States Anti-Doping Agency, orUSADA, called the story \\\"crushing\\\" and claimed that the world and Chinese anti-doping associations had \\\"secretly, until now, swept these positives under the carpet.\\\"\", \"from\": 6967, \"to\": 7194, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6967, \"end\": 6980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Travis Tygart\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Travis_Tygart\"}, {\"begin\": 6993, \"end\": 7025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"United States Anti-Doping Agency\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 6993, \"end\": 7025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"United States Anti-Doping Agency\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_Anti-Doping_Agency\"}, {\"begin\": 7095, \"end\": 7102, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9978782890361554, \"rank\": 0.0021099362914198797, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"CEO\", \"from\": 6982, \"to\": 6985}, {\"ngram\": \"orUSADA\", \"from\": 7027, \"to\": 7034}, {\"ngram\": \"the story\", \"from\": 7043, \"to\": 7052}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 7081, \"to\": 7090}, {\"ngram\": \"these positives\", \"from\": 7160, \"to\": 7175}, {\"ngram\": \"the carpet\", \"from\": 7182, \"to\": 7192}]}, {\"sentence\": \"FairSport and Global Athlete insist Wada's process was \\\"inherently flawed from the outset due to its limited scope and independence\\\".\", \"from\": 7196, \"to\": 7329, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"FairSport\", \"from\": 7196, \"to\": 7205}, {\"ngram\": \"Global Athlete\", \"from\": 7210, \"to\": 7224}, {\"ngram\": \"Wada's process\", \"from\": 7232, \"to\": 7246}, {\"ngram\": \"the outset\", \"from\": 7275, \"to\": 7285}, {\"ngram\": \"its limited scope\", \"from\": 7293, \"to\": 7310}, {\"ngram\": \"independence\", \"from\": 7315, \"to\": 7327}]}, {\"sente